      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks that makes sense. i missed that delete. but what if we have other parts of the code where we aren't using raw pointers? like if we use smart pointers or something, would we still need to worry about these kinds of \"hidden\" memory consumption issues, or does that handle it automatically?",
      "source": "evaluator"
